AlgorithmicDefinition: As a general rule, I have always considered it advisable to use at least $1,500 capital for every 100 bales of Cotton traded in and to limit stop loss orders to not more than 30 points on every 100 bales.

AlgorithmicDefinition: Whatever amount of capital you use to trade with, follow this rule: Divide your capital into 10 equal parts and never risk more than 10% of your capital on any one trade.

AlgorithmicDefinition: Should you lose for 3 consecutive times, then reduce your trading unit and only risk 10% of your remaining capital.
